SIMPLE: elaborate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elaborate
<hw>E*lab"o*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>elaboratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>elaborare</ets> to work out;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>laborare</ets> to labor, <ets>labor</ets> labor.
See <er>Labor</er>.]</ety> <def>Wrought with labor; finished with great
care; studied; executed with exactness or painstaking; <as>as, an
<ex>elaborate</ex> discourse; an <ex>elaborate</ex> performance;
<ex>elaborate</ex> research.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drawn to the life in each <qex>elaborate</qex> page.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Labored; complicated; studied; perfected;
high-wrought.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>E*lab"o*rate*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>E*lab"o*rate*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaborate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Elaborate
<hw>E*lab"o*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Elaborated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Elaborating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To produce with labor</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They in full joy <qex>elaborate</qex> a sigh,</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To perfect with painstaking; to improve or refine
with labor and study, or by successive operations; <as>as, to
<ex>elaborate</ex> a painting or a literary work</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sap is . . . still more <qex>elaborated</qex> and exalted as
it circulates through the vessels of the plant.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elaboration</ent>⟦br⟧
